The undo command, u, restores a session from a pair of backup files that
were created in the configuration directory with the backup command, b.
Type u to undo, i.e., to restore a saved backup.  Please note: existing
data in the current edit session will be overwritten.  After a successful
restore in autosave mode, or on normal program termination, the backup
files will be deleted.  When autosave is enabled, several commands
will automatically perform a backup before they execute.  The commands
protected by autosave are: d, ek, fi, fo, mx, vs, bpf, hpf, and lpf.

